Figs 
<number box="[215,260,784,808]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" value="3.735" valueMax="4.47" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[271,300,784,808]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 55" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1704,1726]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1682]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[152,1434,193,1683]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 55. Male genitalia of species of Argyrogrammana collected at the PNSD. 46. A. alstonii. 47. A. nurtia ludibunda. 48. A. pulchra. 49. A. bonita. 50. A. amalfreda. 51. A. physis phyton. 52. A. halli sp. nov. paratype. 53. A. celata. 54. A. gallardi sp. nov. paratype from PNSD. 55. A. aparamilla. Left to right: dorsal view of uncus, lateral view of tegumen, saccus, uncus, gnathos, valva and aedeagus, and ventral view of valva. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233292/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">47</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,855,1096]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">
In 
<number box="[184,240,856,880]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" value="2013.0">2013</number>
three males were collected exhibiting hilltoping behavior one meter from the ground around 
<number box="[1319,1347,855,880]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" value="15.0">15</number>
:00h. In 
<number box="[151,207,892,916]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" value="2014.0">2014</number>
more three specimens were collected exhibiting the same behavior and at the same time observed on 
<number box="[1346,1406,892,916]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" value="2013.0">2013</number>
. The specimens from 
<collectionCode box="[385,457,928,952]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">PNSD</collectionCode>
are more similar to the 
<typeStatus box="[722,770,928,952]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Brevignon &amp; Gallard, 1995" authorityName="Brevignon &amp; Gallard" authorityYear="1995" box="[807,1340,927,952]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nurtia" subSpecies="ludibunda">
<emphasis box="[807,1027,927,952]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">A. nurtia ludibunda</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Brevignon" box="[1033,1340,927,952]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" refString="Brevignon, C. &amp; Gallard, J. - Y. (1995) Contribuition a l'etude des Riodinidae de Guyane Francaise. Le genre Argyrogrammana Strand, 1932. Lambillionea, 95, 393 - 406." type="journal article" year="1995">
Brévignon &amp; Gallard, 
<number box="[1284,1340,927,952]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
than the nominative subspecies. They differ from the latter by the reduced orange markings, blue patch thinner on the forewing upperside, and the reduced blue markings in both wings underside. Specimens from 
<collectionCode box="[1229,1300,1000,1024]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">PNSD</collectionCode>
are slightly different of the 
<typeStatus box="[332,430,1036,1061]" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[472,697,1036,1061]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="nurtia" subSpecies="ludibunda">
<emphasis box="[472,697,1036,1061]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="231">A. nurtia ludibunda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in size and shape of the blue patch of forewing upperside, even though, no differences were observed in the morphology of the genitalia.
</paragraph>
